text: Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, watch out for this guy.
speaker: A
translation: Hov, hov, hov, hov, pas på ham her.

text: Dwight Schrute in the building. This is Ryan, the new temp.
speaker: A
translation: Dwight Schrute i bygningen. Dette er Ryan, den nye vikar.

text: What's up?
speaker: B
translation: Hvad sker der?

text: Nice to meet you.
speaker: C
translation: Rart at møde dig.

text: Introduce yourself, be polite.
speaker: A
translation: Præsentér dig selv, vær høflig.

text: Dwight Schrute, assistant regional manager.
speaker: B
translation: Dwight Schrute, assisterende regionschef.

text: Assistant to the regional manager.
speaker: A
translation: Assistent for den regionale leder.

text: So Dwight, tell them about the kung fu and the car and everything
speaker: A
translation: Så Dwight, fortæl dem om kung fu og bilen og det hele.

text: Yeah, I got a 78 280Z.
speaker: B
translation: Ja, jeg har en 280Z fra 78.

text: I bought it for 1,200, fixed it up, so now we're 3 grand.
speaker: B
translation: Jeg købte den for 1.200, satte den i stand, så nu er vi oppe på 3.000.

text: That is his profit.
speaker: A
translation: Det er hans fortjeneste.

text: Yeah. New engine, suspension, I got a respray. I got some photos.
speaker: B
translation: Ja, ja. Ny motor, affjedring, jeg har fået en ny lakering. Jeg har nogle billeder.

text: Oh, damn it! Jim!
speaker: B
translation: Åh, for helvede! Jim!

text: Okay, hold on, hold on. Judge is in session. What is the problem here?
speaker: A
translation: Okay, vent lidt, vent lidt. Dommeren er i session. Hvad er problemet her?

text: He put my stuff in Jell-O again.
speaker: B
translation: Han puttede mine ting i Jell-O igen.

text: That's real professional. Thanks
speaker: B
translation: Det er virkelig professionelt. Tak for det

text: This is the third time, and it wasn't funny the first two times either.
speaker: B
translation: Det er tredje gang, og det var heller ikke sjovt de første to gange.

text: What is that?
speaker: A
translation: Hvad er det?

text: It's my staple.
speaker: B
translation: Det er min basisvare.

text: No, no, no, no! Do not take it out.
speaker: A
translation: Nej, nej, nej, nej! Du må ikke tage den ud.

text: You have to eat it out of there, because there are starving people in the world, which I hate, and it is a waste of that kind of food.
speaker: A
translation: Man er nødt til at spise det derude, for der er sultende mennesker i verden, hvilket jeg hader, og det er spild af den slags mad.

text: Okay, you know what? You can be a witness. Can you reprimand him, please?
speaker: B
translation: Okay, ved du hvad? Du kan være vidne. Kan du irettesætte ham?

text: How do you know it was me?
speaker: D
translation: Hvordan ved du, at det var mig?

text: It's always you. Are you gonna discipline him or not?
speaker: B
translation: Det er altid dig. Vil du disciplinere ham eller ej?

text: Ooh, discipline. Kinky!
speaker: A
translation: Åh, disciplin. Kinky!

text: All right, here's the deal, you guys.
speaker: A
translation: Okay, nu skal I høre.

text: The thing about a practical joke is that you have to know when to start as well as when to stop.
speaker: A
translation: Det særlige ved en practical joke er, at man både skal vide, hvornår man skal starte, og hvornår man skal stoppe.

text: Yeah.
speaker: B
translation: Ja.

text: And, yeah Jim. Now is the time to stop putting Dwight's personal effects into Jell-O.
speaker: A
translation: Og ja, Jim. Nu er det tid til at stoppe med at putte Dwights personlige ejendele i Jell-O.

text: Okay. Dwight, I'm sorry, because I've always been your biggest flan.
speaker: D
translation: Ja, okay. Dwight, jeg er ked af det, for jeg har altid været din største fan.

text: Oh, nice!
speaker: A
translation: Åh, dejligt!

text: That's the way it is around here. Just kind of goes around and around and around.
speaker: A
translation: Det er sådan, det er her omkring. Det går bare rundt og rundt og rundt.

text: You, you should have put him in custody.
speaker: C
translation: Du skulle have anholdt ham.

text: Oh, hey! Yes! New guy! And he scores!
speaker: A
translation: Åh, hey! Ja, ja! Ny fyr! Og han scorer!

text: Okay, that's great. I guess what I'm most concerned with is damage to company property.
speaker: B
translation: Okay, det er fint. Det, jeg er mest bekymret for, er vel skader på virksomhedens ejendom.

text: That's all.
speaker: B
translation: Det er alt.

text: Pudding. Pudding
speaker: A
translation: Pudding. Pudding

text: I'm trying to think of another dessert to do.
speaker: A
translation: Jeg prøver at finde på en anden dessert at lave.
